Call me unlucky (because I am), but on average, Malise would be resisted 2 of 3 times. Woohoo, I get to cast a non resisted malise for only 180 mana...and even when malise sticks, I get spells that have a max dmg of 176 doing only 10 dmg...what a deal! I have not encountered any mobs (yet) that resist this much. Frankly, static spawn or not, the exp sucks horribly when you end up constantly wasting tons and tons of mana on these (mega downtime). And I also dont see how you can simply pull with malise, nuke once and then start medding, then nuke again. No matter what level of fire pet you cast, you have to heal it at least once...and ANY time you sit to med you will get agro. And if you sit to far back, you cannot use /pet health report and also the pets life bar is mega lagged. The gorlas are OK, but they arent cracked up to be the rave that ppl try to make them out to be. Supposedly the cougars in IC never resist anything and are easy to single pull all day along the shore...same with dire wolves. This may be due to the fact that the person who was fighting them was a necro (posion based spells), but I don't know and am going to test it myself. I have 185 int with +140 mana and I end up wasting up to 50% mana sometimes on ONE gorla...and thats just pathetic. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uadabpyron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adab Pyron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(12/15/01 2:09:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=212.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/sarfa2001/AdabPyronofTunare.html WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: One Question</span><hr size=1> Sorry you had a bad experiance there Xanthis.  Not sure what your doing wrong but I suspect your a) Nuking too soon(I would let pet taunt once or twice, nuke, sit, wait and nuke again) b) You either don't have the focus item for your fire pet or you aren't holding it when summoning your pet.  As for Golras resisting malise. yes they have moderate resist for their level but its been a while since I was there, they could have upped their resist.  You should at lvl 32 only be spendinfg about 15-20% max per golra.  I had 200 int + mana stuff at that level so your percentage of mana used should be a little higher if you are not what I was at then. (This is Sarfa by the way, this is my mage, Sarfa is my Necromancer.)  And for the previous poster, fire pets DS is not considered damage done my the pet, or anyone for that matter, same as any DS cast on anyone/thing, it counts as environmental damage I believe(such as falling).  By the way, this guide may not be as effective now that Fire Pet's DS's have been nerfed.  Luckily I was able to get through all those level before then. (If you haven't heard, pets that cast DS's including the epic pet sometimes take up to and beyond 20 minutes now, nowhere near as fast as 30 seconds max back when I was fighting with Fire pets)  And for Murlow, yes there was a romaing mob or maybe two if I'm not mistaked at the 1st eti cave mentioned in DL, but thankfully they don't pop very often.  If im'm not mistaken their spawn time is 2.5 hours OR they spawn just as fast and roam off and as long as they are not killed they wander until they are killed, causing them to pop again in the back of the cave.  As for a safe spot to pull in the cave, just pull to a room wall, as you know the yeti's cave &gt;tiny&lt; aggro ranges and if you pull there the only add you might get is the widow/drolvarg roamer(s), and only them because they have a loarger aggro radius. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uadabpyron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adab Pyron</A> at: 12/15/01 2:15:04 am<br></i></td></tr></tabl